post.title: Training At TWU
post.content:
ThoughtWorks University training , is a very different experience. Talk about diversity, our batch of 14 people including one 1 U.S. participant , have trainers from Netherlands( who likes to hand out dropjes ) , from australia (who likes to impersonate/enact clients, P.M.s, and meetings for making the concepts clear to us) , from london (who plays basketball with me, who is also a PC gamer), and from India. We have training at Hotel Royal Orchid, (imba lunches and breakfasts), and here are some photos snapped during sessions.

 

Check the same photos on Facebook : http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?pid=2631903&l=69d71df328&id=815596121

 

 

 

 My China Clay Phone developed over Evolving requirements

 

 

 

 

Ice Cream meter = logs late comers = too many late comings and u end up sponsoring the ice cream treat for the weekend for the team

 

 

 

 

Puzzles, Parking for questions and Accomplishments Post-its

 

 

 

 

After 2 weeks!

 

 

 

 

Agile Software development session.
4 iterations (3 mins / iteration build time ) (= 12 mins).
Changing requirements.
Continuous client feedback. etc etc blah blah...

 

 

 

 

Our pizza delivery system... it will suck if implemented as per our specifications!
